    verification rscReviewGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c200-51627384c00a"; :>> title = "Sprint 200 review gate"; :>> createdAt = "2026-07-09"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "Reviewed. The change does exactly what the honest scope allows: it locks the STRUCTURALLY-VISIBLE half of research-spike routing (a spike's charter must be a legitimate governing source) as a declared warning rule, reusing the D0105/D0107 declared-rules substrate (whereKind + charterTargetType are general, not one-offs). It correctly did NOT overclaim issue061 (part 1 needs a real design session) and did NOT force the un-gatable conversational half into a false control. The mid-implement allow-list widening (Issue|Decision -> the D0068 union) shows the rule earning its keep by catching a real edge case (sr19SpikeStory) during dogfood. Warning-first is the right trust posture. Clean."; }
