    verification rscRetroGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c200-51627384c00e"; :>> title = "Sprint 200 retro gate (autonomous, D0049)"; :>> createdAt = "2026-07-09"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "Autonomous retro (D0049). WELL: the enforceable half of research-spike routing is now a declared control (not just triage vigilance), built on reusable scope/predicate primitives (whereKind, charterTargetType) that grow the declared-rules vocabulary for future migrations. Dogfooding the rule against the live repo caught a real allow-list gap BEFORE commit (sr19SpikeStory) — the rule earned trust immediately. AVOIDABLE-ISSUE SCAN: the first-cut allow-list was too narrow because I anchored on issue055's headline (Issue/proposed-Decision) rather than the guards.rs charter message's full union — LESSON: derive an allow-list from the authoritative predicate (the guard message), not an issue's summary. No defect escaped (caught in implement). Estimate 2 pt held. NEXT: part 1 of issue061 (real-design dogfood); a possible follow-on is promoting researchSpikeCharterRule from warning to a hard guard once a run of clean commits proves it low-noise (the D0102 path)."; }
